-- Japanese Bought Net 56 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2012-11-07T23:53:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-07/japanese-bought-net-56-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Nov. 2 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 56 billion yen ($700.5 million)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 16.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 28.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 11 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 93.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 27.7 billion yen in stocks, and sold 0.3 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 65.8
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
